/font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=69.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.Strike9.com/eq/Maverness/fullsize/Mavermage/NewMaver.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: reasons for pvp</span><hr size=1>   Here are my experiences being a mage on a pvp server. I think that most of pvp is preparation, and knowledge about other classes. Mages are a class that has to seriously prep for pvp. No mage is ready for pvp right after we zone, we need to get pet up, buff pet, gear pet( now that Luclin has resist gear). It takes a few minutes for a mage to be ready to kill people. If an epic wizzie or any class caught me before I was prepped for pvp, they would definitely have the upper hand. <br>
<br>
 Another thing about pvp is the bag of tricks. How many people know about the staff of symbols? Yes, mages can summon a staff with 1 insta cast charge of cancel magic( altough I much prefer golem wands). Rule 1 of pvp: ALWAYS dispell your opponent. Why people let druids keep their sow, and epic wizzies their rune I have no clue. I carry around a tink bag full of potions and stuff to help out in pvp. Its not cheating, but its compensating for weaknesses that my class has. <br>
<br>
     My strategy against epic wizzies is to keep them off their feet. First thing I ALWAYS do against them is to scrub them with golem wands. I make sure that pet is not attacking so I don't poof him since Verant doesn't want to fix that bug. A geared epic pet, with velocity is pretty hard to root. Along with my lvl 8 shock DD, that makes it even harder for them to land a root. If the wizzie lands root, POOF, I dispell it. I'll occasionally cast scars or sirocco to keep the wizzie moving, but I force them to focus only on my pet since their DDs can drop me fast. <br>
<br>
 As for other classes. Bards own mages in pvp simply because they can bug our pets by charming them. No other reason. Rogues will own a mage if the mage stands still( or the rogue gets a lucky duelist on a sitting mage). I wear thurg ring 8, and normally have my lvl 56 DS on( total of a 41DS), so any rogue trying to kill me is going to die way before I do. Rangers are a problem because of snare, but dispell usually takes care of that. Same thing with druids. Sks are the only melees that I really am careful around simply cause of HT( fortunately most SKs I have encountered are dependant upon it). Warriors/monks cannot stop my pet's melee, so I let pet kill them while I run my ass around trying to stay alive. Clerics and Paladins are boring simply cause of their healing power, and NEED to have mala dropped on them. I carry around the mage wand from hate simply so I can drop alot of fast damage and kill them cause they like to wait till they are low health before they heal( though the lvl8 shock works well also). Against enchanters, its all about dispelling. Their nukes are weak, and they'll probably go oom before they can land a killing blow. Dispell a necro's dots, and kill their pet, and they are dead. <br>
<br>
 Mages don't suck at pvp once we go epic. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>  <img src ="http://www.strike9.com/eq/Maverness/fullsize/Mavermage/Najena_sig.jpg">
